# ─── PulseMarkets — Environment Variables ────────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your keys.
# Expo reads variables prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ and inlines them at build
# time via `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_*`.  No extra config in app.json needed.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env to version control.
#            Add `.env` to .gitignore (already done in this repo).
#
# ─── Market Data Provider ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The app picks the first key that is set, in this order:
#   1. EXPO_PUBLIC_POLYGON_API_KEY   → Polygon.io provider
#   2. EXPO_PUBLIC_FINNHUB_API_KEY   → Finnhub provider
#   3. (neither set)                 → built-in Mock provider (no network, offline safe)
#
# ─── Option A: Finnhub (recommended for free-tier real-time data) ─────────────
#
#   Signup : https://finnhub.io/register
#   Plan   : Free tier — 60 calls/min, real-time US quotes, no card required
#   Limits : Each getQuote() uses 2 API calls (quote + 30-day candle for volume).
#            For batches >20 symbols you may occasionally hit the 60 req/min cap.
#            The alert engine polls every 30 s and fetches one symbol at a time,
#            so free tier is more than sufficient for typical usage.
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_FINNHUB_API_KEY=

# ─── Option B: Polygon.io ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   Signup : https://polygon.io/dashboard/signup
#   Plan   : Starter (free) — EOD/delayed data, 5 req/min
#             Basic  ($29/mo) — real-time snapshots, unlimited calls
#   Notes  : On the free plan getQuote() returns the previous day's close, not
#             a live price.  Upgrade to Basic for real-time alert evaluation.
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_POLYGON_API_KEY=

# ─── Backend API (optional — only needed if running the FastAPI backend) ───────
#
# The backend at /backend/ runs a server-side alert engine and handles push
# notification delivery.  The mobile app works fully offline (mock data) or
# with a real market provider without the backend.
#
# To run the backend locally:
#   cd backend
#   pip install -r requirements.txt
#   uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
#
# Then expose it to your phone (same network or via a tunnel):
#   npx localtunnel --port 8000   →  copy the HTTPS URL below
#
# The value is already set in app.json under expo.extra.apiBaseUrl for local
# testing.  Override it here if you want a different URL at dev time.
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://your-tunnel-url.loca.lt/api/v1
